# 12-Month Excel Training Course for Beginners

This 12-month Excel training plan is designed for individuals with little to no prior experience in Excel. Each month focuses on key foundational and intermediate skills, building progressively toward advanced applications such as data analysis, dashboards, and automation. Every section includes hands-on practice and step-by-step instructions.

---

## Month 1: Introduction to Excel Interface
- Open Excel and explore the Ribbon, Tabs, and Quick Access Toolbar.
- Learn how to save, open, and close workbooks.
- Understand worksheets, columns, rows, and cells.
- Enter basic data into cells (text, numbers, and dates).
- Adjust column width and row height.
- Practice using Undo, Redo, and Autofill.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Tutorial for Beginners by Kevin Stratvert](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LgXzzu68j7M)

---

## Month 2: Formatting and Basic Operations
- Apply cell formatting: bold, italic, underline, borders, and fill color.
- Use alignment and text wrapping tools.
- Format numbers as currency, percentages, or dates.
- Merge and center titles.
- Practice basic formulas: =SUM(), =AVERAGE(), =MIN(), =MAX().
- Use AutoSum to quickly total rows and columns.

