---

## Month 3: Relative and Absolute References
- Understand the difference between relative, absolute ($A$1), and mixed references.
- Create formulas that reference multiple cells or sheets.
- Use the Fill Handle to copy formulas correctly.
- Practice linking data between sheets.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Beginner Tutorial by Learnit Training](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=310z5K14JXw)

---

## Month 4: Data Entry and Cleaning
- Use Find & Replace and Go To Special.
- Remove duplicates and blank rows.
- Use TRIM(), PROPER(), UPPER(), and LOWER() functions to clean text.
- Sort and filter data alphabetically or numerically.
- Practice data validation (drop-down lists, restrictions).

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Tutorial for Beginners (Made Easy) by MyOnlineTrainingHub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fzdn1vcHPsA)

---

## Month 5: Charts and Visualization
- Insert and customize column, line, and pie charts.
- Add chart titles, legends, and axis labels.
- Format chart elements (colors, styles, layouts).
- Use sparklines for mini trend visuals.
- Practice selecting the right chart for different datasets.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Tutorial for Beginners by Kevin Stratvert (Charts Section)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LgXzzu68j7M)

---

## Month 6: Intermediate Formulas
- Practice using IF(), COUNTIF(), and SUMIF().
- Use nested IF() statements.
- Understand logical operators (> < = <>).
- Learn about text functions: LEFT(), RIGHT(), MID(), CONCAT().

