---

## Month 7: Working with Tables
- Convert data ranges into Tables (Ctrl + T).
- Use structured references in formulas.
- Apply Table styles and filters.
- Add calculated columns and Total Rows.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Get Ahead FAST! Excel Express Tutorial for BEGINNERS! by Teacherâ€™s Tech](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p_NvzCJ31D0)

---

## Month 8: PivotTables and PivotCharts
- Insert a PivotTable from raw data.
- Drag and drop fields into Rows, Columns, Values, and Filters.
- Summarize data by count, sum, and average.
- Group data by month or category.
- Create a PivotChart from the same dataset.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Pivot Table Excel Tutorial by Kevin Stratvert](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m0wI61ahfLc)

---

## Month 9: Lookup and Reference Functions
- Use VLOOKUP() to find values in tables.
- Learn the benefits of XLOOKUP() and INDEX-MATCH().
- Troubleshoot #N/A and #REF! errors.
- Practice cross-sheet lookups using named ranges.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Tutorial from Basic to Advanced for Data Analyst by Satish Dhawale](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XbyiTh-6k9Q)

---

## Month 10: Data Analysis Tools
- Use conditional formatting to highlight key data points.
- Apply color scales and icon sets for trends.
- Use the Data Analysis Toolpak for descriptive statistics.
- Create scenarios and use Goal Seek.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Excel Tutorial for Beginners (Made Easy) by MyOnlineTrainingHub](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fzdn1vcHPsA)

---

## Month 11: Dashboards and Reporting
- Combine charts, slicers, and PivotTables into a dashboard.
- Use shapes and icons for professional layout.
- Link summary tables to source data.
- Add dynamic titles and interactive elements.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Hands-On Excel Tutorial Beginner to Pro Course (2024) by Pragmatic Works](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dxKK3rbubvo)

---

## Month 12: Automation and Advanced Topics
- Record and run basic macros.
- Use relative references in macro recording.
- Intro to Power Query for importing and cleaning data.
- Review advanced formula combinations (INDEX-MATCH, IFERROR, etc.).
- Capstone Project: Create a personal dashboard using learned skills.

ðŸŽ¥ Watch: [Hands-On Excel Tutorial Beginner to Pro Course (2024) by Pragmatic Works](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dxKK3rbubvo)

---

By the end of this program, you will be confident in data organization, analysis, visualization, and automation using Excel. Continue practicing with real-world datasets and explore Power BI, VBA, or advanced analytics for further growth.
